cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dialogue state tracking, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as DST is an important component of conversational agents and chatbots, which are AI applications. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed framework uses weighted system utterances to identify relevant context, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new framework for DST, which could have implications for software development of conversational agents. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also less likely but relevant as the paper deals with improving the user experience of conversational agents by better understanding the relevant context of the conversation.
